<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="876" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/422.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s July 19. Under bank agreement, Erlanger’s interest for
                            current quarter will be advanced to Sharp August 15 for immediate
                            transmission. Clark urges that bankers arrange with Erlanger to hold
                            advance here, or, failing this, he be permitted to <pb facs="0801" n="685" xml:id="pg_685"/> offset payment against interest on new
                            loan. Receivership crippled if Liberian Government forced to pay double
                            interest. Ready money imperatively needed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chum.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>